(8620, 1, '2017-09-01 02:59:02', '2017-09-01 02:59:02', 'There’s nothing we love more than a bride who loves to experiment. She knows all the “wedding rules” (red lehenga for the wedding, hair up in a bun) but the cool new bride of 2018 will ditch these expectations to create her own fabulous wedding!\r\n\r\nStep one: give your wedding colour palate a surprising makeover. In 2017, the Indian bridal lehenga market exploded with colours we’d only seen in the movies. Royal reds made way for blushy lavenders, classy golds and unusual blues and greens. For 2018, we’re wishing for this trend to grow and for new colours to take over our Instagram feeds and Pinterest boards. Bookmark this list of the hottest new colours that will be big in 2018 and add them to your wedding inspiration boards today!', '8 Bridal Lehenga Colours That Will Be Big In 2018', 'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Proin tincidunt nunc lorem, nec faucibus mi facilisis eget. Mauris laoreet, nisl id faucibus pellentesque, mi mi tempor enim, sit amet interdum felis nibh a leo.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '8-bridal-lehenga-colours-that-will-be-big-in-2018', '', '', '2018-08-09 08:24:58', '2018-08-09 08:24:58', '', 0, 'http://wedesignthemes.com/themes/malar/non-formal-education-reach-out-to-underprivileged-copy/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(8622, 1, '2017-09-01 01:00:00', '2017-09-01 01:00:00', 'Air conditioners are the most purchased appliance during the summers. However, an AC can only work optimally only if you take proper care of it. A dirty AC can lead to various infections and diseases. Which is why air conditioner cleaning and servicing is important both before and after the AC season. But what happens if we don’t get it serviced regularly? One of the most common problem people face is that their AC starts smelling foul. This happens mostly due to mould and bacterial growth in the AC air ducts. So, if your AC is stinking, get an AC duct cleaning done. But first, what causes this foul smell? Let’s find out.\r\n<h2>Top 3 Reasons Why Your AC is Stinking</h2>\r\n<strong>1. When your AC smells of DIRTY SOCKS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>The first reason why your AC is blowing smelly air is due to a build-up of mold (a type of fungi) and bacteria inside the AC duct. Disease-causing bacteria and molds are harmful to human health.\r\n\r\nAll air conditioners work by converting hot air into cold air. This process leads to condensation and formation of little droplets of water inside the AC unit. These droplets of water should drain out via the AC duct but at times the moisture and leftover water cause fungus and bacteria to grow inside the AC ducts. This causes a foul moldy stink in your AC which is similar to the smell of dirty, old socks. A stinking AC calls for air conditioner cleaning and maintenance.\r\n\r\n<em>Pro tip:</em> You will notice some greenish-black accumulation on the pipes and the ducts if there is a mold infestation. To prevent this get AC duct cleaning done regularly.', 'Air Conditioner Cleaning: 3 Reasons Why Your AC Is Stinking', 'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Proin tincidunt nunc lorem, nec faucibus mi facilisis eget. Mauris laoreet, nisl id faucibus pellentesque, mi mi tempor enim, sit amet interdum felis nibh a leo.', 'publish', 'open', 'open',